text.__SUMMARY__: Acer tibetense is an uncommon Asian species of maple. It has been found only in Tibet.Acer tibetense is a deciduous  tree up to 10 meters tall. Leaves are non-compound, up to 9 cm wide and 8 cm across, thin, usually with 3 lobes but no teeth.
